= Userspace Documentation
:toc: left
:icons: font
:sectlinks:

See also: link:../index.html[Home], link:../building.html[Build Guide], link:../kernel/index.html[Kernel Documentation]

This section documents Valkyrie userspace components by source directory. Each page below maps to a directory under `usr/` and summarizes its purpose and role in runtime testing.

== Userspace Components

* link:libmath.html[libmath.ad] — Minimal shared math library for userspace
* link:sh.html[sh.ad] — Interactive shell userspace program
* link:selftest.html[selftest.ad] — Syscall-based userspace self-test program
* link:test.html[test.ad] — Legacy test directory (compatibility/transition)

== Navigation Notes

* Start with link:selftest.html[selftest.ad] if you are validating syscall and context-switch behavior.
* See link:../kernel/syscall.html[kernel/syscall.ad] for kernel-side syscall handling details.
* For build integration, see link:../building.html[building.ad] and `usr/SConscript`.

